Establish and maintain a Project Implementation Unit
Establish and maintain a Project Management Unit
Establish and maintain in each participating district a District Project Planning Secretariat and a District Implementation Unit
Establish and maintain in each participating province a Provincial Coordination Committee

title.narrative: % decrease in number of violent conflict incidents

comment.narrative: Based on data from five districts in Maluku for issues related to conflicts. MCLE only operated in Maluku since 2010
21 % decrease in number of violent conflict incidents. Source: national violence monitoring system database,http://www.snpk-indonesia.com/
Based on NMC annual report, all participating districts and project team at central llevel used data from the MIS as the mainsource for monitoring and reports.

title.narrative: # Recommendations by Business-Government forums for regulatory improvements available in seven districts.

comment.narrative: Based on PSD Final Report 2011, the recommendations by Business-Government Forum with regards to regulatory improvement wereavailable in five districts (Alor, TTS, Lembata, Belu, Maluku Tengah)

title.narrative: Improved access to cost effective, high-quality rural infrastructure (ERR>20%) through participatory planning processes in 8 provinces

comment.narrative: Based on assessment of 32 infrastructure sub-projects in eight provinces. The results are similar to PNPM survey, a full EIRRstudyreport was therefore not launched. All SPADA sub-projects used planning participatory process(source: assessment report byKPDT)

title.narrative: % of planned annual financing for sub-district grants disbursed

actual.value: 100% for 2007 cycle; 100% for 2008 cycle; 100% for 2009 cycle, 100% for 2010 cycle

comment.narrative: Based on data source from project MIS. The sub district grants include planning grant and block grant. No disbursement in 2011

actual.value: 100% for 2007 cycle; 96% for 2008 cycle; 100% for 2009 cycle; 100% for 2010 cycle; and 100% for 2011 cycle. (incl. grants fortop-up activities)

comment.narrative: Based on data source from project MIS. The sub district grants include planning grant and block grant.

title.narrative: % of district infrastructure quality classified as "satisfactory" to "excellent"

comment.narrative: Based on data source from project MIS. Through output study, an independent firm was conducting assessment to reviewinfrastructurequality and local government follow up for asset inventory and operation and maintenance cost. The result showed96.4% of infrastructure sub project was maintained

title.narrative: #Assessments of obstacles to local private sector development completed

comment.narrative: Based on data source from project MIS.

comment.narrative: Based on data source from project MIS.
Based on data source from project MIS.

title.narrative: # teachers, principals and education committee members trained.

comment.narrative: Based on project MIS, the achievement including beneficiaries from additional/top up activities in 2011

title.narrative: # health and education committees trained and established involving range of government and non-government actors

comment.narrative: Based on project MIS, this includes 26 health committees and 32 education committees

title.narrative: Baseline and impact surveys and thematic studies completed.

target.value: 3 baseline and impact surveys and studies

comment.narrative: Including GSD survey in 2008, two assessments to investment climate (2009), study on participatory planning (2011), and study ofproject outputs (Oct 2012).

title.narrative: % Increase in national primary school test scores in participating districts

actual.value: Decreased 5% for elementary school and increase 6% for junior high school

comment.narrative: Reduction of primary school test scores due to changing policy on national test score. Source: WB-Education Database

title.narrative: % of planned consultants are in place at start of annual cycle.

comment.narrative: Source: Project MIS

title.narrative: # persons benefiting from legal aid, case handling assistance through the project.

comment.narrative: The figure, while appearing way in excess of the target, is the total beneficiaries involved in the 32 cases handled by MCLEprogram. Source: MCLE Final Report 2011.
ased on data source from project MIS.

title.narrative: % of sub-district infrastructure quality classified as "satisfactory" to "excellent".
Increased use of Alternative Dispute Resolution and Legal mechanism by communities to resolve disputes peacefully in Makulu province

Business registrations increased more than 73% in the 20 target districts. Cumulative number of registration 2007-2010: 14,482.Source: PSD Final Report 2011

comment.narrative: The new patients increased 41%; calculated based on secondary data from Ministry of Health. Source: Provincial Health Profile
